<br>
It's a fictional account of a fourth wise man (Martin Sheen) who was late to a meeting with the other three. They leave without him. This 4th wise man and his servant then go alone to find the messiah. <br>
<br>
The Sheen character has three jewels for the baby. He doesnt find the baby and continues the search which takes him his whole life. Through it he uses the jewels to help people, feed people &amp; ends up with lepers in Jerusalem at the time of Jesus' crucifixtion. But he's old &amp; sick. He has one jewel left that he tries to give to Jesus on the way to calvary, but he uses the jewel to pay the debt of a father whose daughter was being taken into slavery.<br>
<br>
He does see Jesus after the resurrection... as 'Sheen' is dying he tells Jesus he had gifts but didn't give them to him. Jesus tells him he did give them; he clothed him when he was naked. fed him when he was hungry etc. 'Sheen' tells him he never did those things. Jesus tells him when ever you did those for the least of his people, he did them for Him.<br>
<br>
<br>
Not accurate to scripture of course, but it has a strong Christian message.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vonalbro>VONALBRO</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style=color:navy;><b>Moderator and,<br>Lady of Good Cheer</b></span></span><br>  Posts: 574<br> <font color=#B87333>(12/19/03 10:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=216.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fourth Wise Man</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/bat3193/smiley6/wave3.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> Wihinape,<br>
